commit.message: Didn't even know the doctests were a thing
Caught a bug in the doctests
maybe more negative test cases should be a thing
maybe more negatives should be a thing
One of the tests was a dup
Make nltk.sentiment.vader deterministic
Added Tom Aarsen to contributors alphabetically

Added tests for the sent_end_chars changes to tokenization

See issue #2586 for more information on the sentences and the desired behaviour.

Reworked the Non Word regex to include newly added punctuation

Non Word regex now includes punctuation added in sent_end_chars in a subclass of PunktLanguageVars, allowing custom punctuation like the Bengali full stop to be handled as a full stop.

Resolved incorrectly named methods causing test failures

setup_class is not automatically called by unittest at the creation of the class instance. setUpClass is.
fix issue to make some translate modules like gleu_score importable
Added Tom Aarsen to contributors alphabetically

Added required pickle import

In commit #2307 the method `save_file` was added with a call to `pickle.dump`, while `pickle` is never imported.

Provided object for method call

`save_file` used to be an imported function, but was changed into a method of the SentimentAnalyzer class in commit #2307, where this reference was left untouched.
